For me, the truly frightening rabbit has martial art skillz, a set of throwing knives, and knows how to slice you up with just about any sharp piece of metal or broken glass. Probably a straight razor or two tucked away, handles any knife with speed.

Short swords work so long as they are light for speed and precision. Perhaps even a rapier. If you can accommodate martial arts of any level, throwing weapons such as stars & shuriken of many flavors. Blow guns and short bows, or small crossbows.

Perhaps fighting claws for hands &/or feet. A kick from a foot equipped with three 6" steel blades would gut most people before they realized they were being attacked. Of course, rabbits would be lightly armored, probably clothing and maybe some leather. A trained rabbit warrior relies on speed, dexterity, movements to deceive the eye and draw the enemy's attention to where the real attack isn't coming from.

If engaging a human-sized foe, slice out the Achilles tendon or hamstring, bring him to the ground where you can reach his throat.

I've focused on hand-to-hand here. Guns and the support equipment for guns would overpower a bun's weight limit so fast they couldn't carry enough to be effective & self-sufficient. Possible option here is sharpshooters sniping from a distance where they could rely on ammo & support gear being carried by beasts of burden. Companion dogs. Horses could carry a lot more equipment if their rider is rabbit-sized.

The horse carries most equipment, the bun is highly mobile at need, the dog can carry small amounts of equipment if necessary for short-range movement, but provides deadly distraction while the rabbit slices and dices when closing hand-to-hand. After getting several rifle or crossbow shots off first.
